ieves different design effects. It shows the conditions under which certain constructions can be employed and why; what criteria such as construction costs, issues of sustainability, of energy efficiency, of assembly or of insulation or protection against moisture can also influence the choice of a system. In addition to classical constructions, Enclose | Build offers a look at future developments. How will the facade evolve as an interface for information? What do viable concepts for environmentally active, energy-efficient building shells look like? Enclose | Build is an indispensable tool for every architect and planner.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aExterior walls. 0aFacades. 0aRoofs. 4aWand. 4abuilding hull. 4aconstruction design. 4aconstruction. 4adesign. 4adetailing. 4afacade construction. 4afacade. 4aroof. 7aARCHITECTURE / General.2bisacsh1 aKrammer, Martin, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aReichel, Alexander, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSchultz, Kerstin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSturm, Jörg, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2015z9783110438642oZDB-23-DKA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG0 cprintz978303460207540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978303560336140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783035603361423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783035603361.jpg  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_AD  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_